            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="./DCP-LETT-8075.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Letter to David Forbes, 18 November [1871]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD argued that the digestive acids of earthworms helped to disintegrate rocks (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, pp. 240–6).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8075.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to David Forbes, 18 November [1871]</ref> and n. 4. ‘Organic acids’ are what CD called ‘humic acid’.</note>
